// Content Sprint 13: Resources and Support.
window.CONTENT_SPRINT_13 = {"operator-resources":{"summary":"Access the working templates, registers, worksheets and launch controls used to plan, configure, test, launch and operate your marketplace. Use each resource alongside the relevant Hub guidance and maintain it as part of your marketplace operating record.","audience":["Marketplace leadership","Marketplace Operations","Seller management","Catalogue","Finance","Technology and integrations","Customer Service","Test and launch teams"],"sections":{"Understand the Operator Toolkit":"\n<p>The Operator Toolkit contains working templates, registers and launch controls used to plan, configure, test, launch and operate the marketplace. These resources support the detailed Hub guidance. They do not replace the approved marketplace decisions or the configured Production environment.</p>\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Working templates</h3><p>Documents and spreadsheets that help teams prepare decisions, collect information and execute repeatable activities.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Official guidance</h3><p>Hub pages and current Marketplacer documentation that explain how the workflow or platform capability operates.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Operating records</h3><p>Registers that preserve owners, decisions, evidence, approval and change history after launch.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Controlled copies</h3><p>Files copied into the Operator’s approved workspace, assigned to an owner and protected according to the information they contain.</p></article></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Use the templates as living records.</strong> Keep them current throughout onboarding, launch and business as usual rather than completing them once and filing them away.</div>\n","Choose the Right Resource for Each Stage":"\n<p>Start with the master implementation tracker, then introduce each resource when the corresponding workstream begins.</p>\n<div class=\"resource-journey\"><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>1</span><strong>Plan</strong><p>Onboarding Checklist and Decision Register</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>2</span><strong>Design</strong><p>Customer Journey and Seller Strategy</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>3</span><strong>Configure</strong><p>Marketplace Configuration Register</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>4</span><strong>Onboard</strong><p>Seller discovery, information and readiness records</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>5</span><strong>Test</strong><p>Strategy, matrix, financial outcome and evidence records</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>6</span><strong>Approve</strong><p>Seller and Production readiness decisions</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>7</span><strong>Launch</strong><p>Runbook, control log, hypercare and BAU handover</p></article></div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Resource type</th><th>Use it when</th><th>Expected outcome</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Checklist</td><td>Several actions, owners and dates must be tracked</td><td>A controlled implementation plan</td></tr><tr><td>Register</td><td>Decisions, evidence or status must remain traceable</td><td>One authoritative operating record</td></tr><tr><td>Worksheet</td><td>A working session must produce an agreed design</td><td>A documented and reviewable output</td></tr><tr><td>Decision record</td><td>Formal approval is required</td><td>A clear Go, Conditional Go, No-Go or defer decision</td></tr><tr><td>Runbook</td><td>Timed actions must be executed in sequence</td><td>A controlled launch or recovery event</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","Plan and Govern the Onboarding Programme":"<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Onboarding governance</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Operator Onboarding Checklist</h3>\n      <p>Track required, recommended and optional activities, owners, due dates, status, questions and blockers.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace programme owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Onboarding governance</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/operator/onboarding/marketplacer-operator-onboarding-checklist.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=onboarding-overview\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Decision governance</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplace Decision Register</h3>\n      <p>Record each marketplace decision, rationale, affected settings, Sellers, integrations, testing impact and approval.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace leadership</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Decision governance</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/operator/decisions/marketplace-decision-register.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=marketplace-decision-register\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Keep tasks and decisions separate.</strong> A task can be completed while its underlying decision is still provisional. The Decision Register makes that dependency visible.</div>","Define the Customer and Seller Strategy":"<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Marketplace design</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Customer Journey Mapping Template</h3>\n      <p>Define Product discovery, checkout, payment, communication, fulfilment, cancellation, return, refund and Customer Service ownership.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Ecommerce and Customer Experience</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Marketplace design</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/operator/customer-journey/marketplacer-customer-journey-mapping-template.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=customer-journey-mapping\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller strategy</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Strategy Worksheet</h3>\n      <p>Define the ideal Seller profile, launch targets, value proposition, commercial model, connection options, onboarding approach and performance expectations.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace leadership and Seller management</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Seller strategy</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/operator/seller-strategy/marketplacer-seller-strategy-worksheet.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-strategy-session\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>","Configure the Marketplace":"<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Configuration control</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplace Configuration Register</h3>\n      <p>Record approved decisions, Sandbox and Production values, marketplace defaults, Seller overrides, evidence, testing status and approver.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace Operations</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Configuration control</dd></div></dl>\n      <p class=\"resource-note\">Production remains the source of truth. Record intentional environment differences rather than assuming both environments are identical.</p>\n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/operator/configuration/marketplace-configuration-register.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=configuration-overview\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Register field</th><th>Why it matters</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Approved decision</td><td>Connects the setting to the operating model</td></tr><tr><td>Sandbox value</td><td>Records the test baseline and refresh exposure</td></tr><tr><td>Production value</td><td>Records the live source of truth</td></tr><tr><td>Seller override</td><td>Makes exceptions visible</td></tr><tr><td>Evidence and test status</td><td>Shows that the resulting behaviour was verified</td></tr><tr><td>Owner and approver</td><td>Keeps change accountability clear</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Onboard and Approve Sellers":"<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller information collection</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Information Questionnaire</h3>\n      <p>Collect business, contact, tax, Product, shipping, return, commercial and payout information.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Seller management</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Seller information collection</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-information-questionnaire.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-information\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Connection discovery</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Technical Discovery Form</h3>\n      <p>Assess the Seller platform, Product and stock source, Order and fulfilment paths, refund integration, technical ownership and testing availability.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Technology and Seller management</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Connection discovery</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-technical-discovery-form.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=product-ingestion\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller readiness</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Readiness Register</h3>\n      <p>Consolidate onboarding, catalogue, commercial, operational, Finance and test evidence for every launch Seller.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Seller launch owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Seller readiness</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-readiness-register.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-launch-readiness\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller approval</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Launch Approval Record</h3>\n      <p>Record the Seller-specific approval, conditions, accepted risks, activation scope and early-life monitoring owner.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace launch authority</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Seller approval</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-launch-approval-record.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-launch-readiness\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>","Test and Approve the Marketplace":"<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Test planning</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Testing Strategy Template</h3>\n      <p>Define scope, risks, roles, environments, evidence, defects, entry criteria and exit criteria.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Test lead</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Test planning</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/testing/strategy/testing-strategy-template.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=testing-strategy\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Scenario management</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Test Matrix</h3>\n      <p>Record scenarios, prerequisites, expected outcomes, actual results, evidence and approval.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Test lead</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Scenario management</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/testing/evidence/test-matrix.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=testing-strategy\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Finance validation</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Expected Financial Outcome Worksheet</h3>\n      <p>Calculate expected commission or wholesale Seller entitlement, Operator result, fees, tax and refunds.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Finance</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Finance validation</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/testing/finance/expected-financial-outcome-worksheet.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=end-to-end-testing\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Evidence control</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Test Evidence Record</h3>\n      <p>Keep traceable screenshots, IDs, timestamps, logs and approvals for each test result.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Test lead</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Evidence control</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/testing/evidence/test-evidence-record.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=testing-strategy\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Defect management</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Defect Register</h3>\n      <p>Track severity, owner, affected scope, fix, retest, regression and closure.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Test and delivery leads</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Defect management</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/testing/defects/defect-register.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=testing-strategy\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Transaction reconciliation</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>End-to-End Transaction Record</h3>\n      <p>Reconcile payment, Marketplacer Order, Seller Invoices, Seller-system Orders, fulfilment, refund, remittance and payout.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace Operations and Finance</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Transaction reconciliation</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/testing/end-to-end/end-to-end-transaction-record.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=end-to-end-testing\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>","Execute Launch and Handover":"<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Marketplace approval</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Production Readiness Register</h3>\n      <p>Consolidate Production configuration, Sellers, catalogue, customer journey, integrations, Finance, support and containment evidence.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Launch manager</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Marketplace approval</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/launch/readiness/production-readiness-register.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=production-readiness\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Launch decision</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Go or No-Go Decision Record</h3>\n      <p>Record launch scope, conditions, accepted risks, decision authority and outcome.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Executive launch authority</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Launch decision</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/launch/readiness/go-or-no-go-decision-record.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=production-readiness\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Launch execution</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Launch-Day Runbook</h3>\n      <p>Sequence launch actions, owners, dependencies, decision points and communication.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Launch manager</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Launch execution</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/launch/runbook/launch-day-runbook.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=go-live\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Launch evidence</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Launch Control Log</h3>\n      <p>Record launch actions, timestamps, observations, decisions, containment and recovery.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Launch control owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Launch evidence</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/launch/runbook/launch-control-log.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=go-live\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Early-life support</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Hypercare Tracker</h3>\n      <p>Track incidents, Seller questions, customer contacts, Product corrections, integration failures and Finance differences.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Hypercare lead</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Early-life support</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/launch/hypercare/hypercare-tracker.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=go-live\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operational handover</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Business-as-Usual Handover Checklist</h3>\n      <p>Confirm permanent owners, procedures, access, monitoring, Finance cadence, support routes and known risks.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace Operations</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Operational handover</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/launch/handover/business-as-usual-handover-checklist.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=daily-operations\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>","Maintain Your Working Resources":"\n<p>Copy each template into the Operator’s approved project location before use. The Hub version remains the clean master template.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Control</th><th>Operator practice</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Ownership</td><td>Assign one accountable owner and a backup owner.</td></tr><tr><td>Version</td><td>Use a clear version or last-reviewed date and avoid parallel uncontrolled copies.</td></tr><tr><td>Access</td><td>Limit Seller, customer, Finance, identity and integration information to authorised users.</td></tr><tr><td>Change history</td><td>Record material changes, rationale, approver and affected environments.</td></tr><tr><td>Evidence</td><td>Retain IDs, reports and links required to support the decision or test result.</td></tr><tr><td>Review</td><td>Revisit the resource when the operating model, platform behaviour or team ownership changes.</td></tr><tr><td>Retention</td><td>Keep launch and operational evidence according to the Operator’s governance requirements.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not store secrets in the templates.</strong> Passwords, MFA recovery codes, API secrets, bank credentials and unrestricted Production exports require approved secure storage.</div>\n"},"related":[["onboarding-overview","Onboarding Overview"],["marketplace-decision-register","Marketplace Decision Register"],["configuration-overview","Configuration Overview"],["testing-strategy","Testing Strategy"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"],["go-live","Go-Live"]]},"training-resources":{"summary":"Follow the Operator learning path, prepare for each training topic, access supporting resources, practise the required activities in Sandbox and use current Marketplacer documentation to reinforce and maintain your team’s capability.","audience":["Marketplace programme owners","Functional managers","Marketplace Operations","Seller management","Catalogue","Finance","Customer Service","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understand the Training Library":"\n<p>The Training Library supports structured learning, hands-on practice and ongoing capability. It combines Operator learning paths, role assignments, preparation activities, Sandbox exercises, competency records and current Marketplacer guidance.</p>\n<div class=\"training-principles-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Learn</h3><p>Understand the marketplace outcome, terminology and approved operating model.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Observe</h3><p>Use a current deck, recording or walkthrough to see the workflow.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Practise</h3><p>Complete a guided activity in Sandbox with representative data.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Demonstrate</h3><p>Show that the task can be completed and the result can be explained.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Apply</h3><p>Move the approved change or procedure into Production through the controlled process.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Refresh</h3><p>Review the topic when the platform, operating model or team changes.</p></article></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Attendance is not competency.</strong> A team member is ready when they can complete the relevant activity, identify the expected outcome and know where to escalate exceptions.</div>\n","Follow the Core Operator Learning Path":"<div class=\"resource-journey\"><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>1</span><strong>Platform foundations</strong><p>Architecture, terminology, Production and Sandbox, access and configuration</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>2</span><strong>Structure and commercials</strong><p>Taxonomy, Product model, commission, wholesale, tax and payment responsibilities</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>3</span><strong>Seller and Product operations</strong><p>Seller onboarding, ingestion, Mapping, Catalog Rules and Product Vetting</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>4</span><strong>Orders and exceptions</strong><p>Order creation, Seller Invoice splitting, fulfilment, cancellations, returns and refunds</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>5</span><strong>Finance and reporting</strong><p>Remittance, payout, reconciliation, reporting and daily operations</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>6</span><strong>Testing and launch</strong><p>Testing sequence, Seller approval, Production Readiness, Go-Live and hypercare</p></article></div><div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Core learning sequence</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Operator Learning Path</h3>\n      <p>Use the recommended topic order and record the practical outcome expected after each stage.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace programme owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Core learning sequence</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/training/learning-paths/operator-learning-path.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=training-programme\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>","Choose Resources by Role":"\n<p>Assign learning according to the responsibilities each person will perform. Use the matrix to distinguish required, recommended and awareness-level learning.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Role</th><th>Priority learning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace leadership</td><td>Architecture, decisions, commercials, readiness and governance</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplace Operations</td><td>Configuration, Sellers, Products, Orders, refunds and daily operations</td></tr><tr><td>Seller management</td><td>Seller lifecycle, onboarding, support boundaries and performance</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Taxonomy, ingestion, Mapping, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting and quality</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Commission, wholesale, tax, refunds, remittance, payout and reconciliation</td></tr><tr><td>Customer Service</td><td>Orders, Shipments, cancellations, returns, refunds and communications</td></tr><tr><td>Ecommerce</td><td>Product discovery, pricing, cart, checkout and customer communications</td></tr><tr><td>Technology and integrations</td><td>Environments, APIs, MConnect, Webhooks, source of truth and recovery</td></tr><tr><td>Security administrators</td><td>Users, roles, MFA, SSO and credentials</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Learning assignment</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Role-Based Learning Matrix</h3>\n      <p>Assign required topics, depth, practical activities and backup coverage by role.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Functional managers</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Learning assignment</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/training/learning-paths/role-based-learning-matrix.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=roles-responsibilities\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n","Prepare Before Training":"\n<p>Preparation should make each training session practical. Before the session, confirm who from your team should attend, that the required access is available, and that you have the marketplace decisions, examples and questions needed to apply the topic to your operating model.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Topic</th><th>Prepare beforehand</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Platform setup</td><td>Operator users, roles, Sandbox access and branding assets</td></tr><tr><td>Commercials</td><td>Proposed commission or wholesale model, tax position and payout process</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Taxonomy, sample Products, Brands and required attributes</td></tr><tr><td>Seller onboarding</td><td>Seller profile, agreement, questionnaire and connection method</td></tr><tr><td>Orders and refunds</td><td>Customer journey, payment flow and support responsibilities</td></tr><tr><td>Integrations</td><td>Architecture, source systems, credentials and technical owners</td></tr><tr><td>Testing</td><td>Launch scope, representative Sellers and expected financial results</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n  <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Session preparation</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n  <h3>Training Preparation Worksheet</h3>\n  <p>Capture attendees, access, sample data, decisions, questions and the practical activity your team should complete.</p>\n  <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace programme owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Preparing your team for training</dd></div></dl>\n  <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/training/activities/training-preparation-worksheet.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=training-programme\">Open guidance</a></div>\n</article></div>\n","Use Session Decks and Recordings":"\n<p>Your Delivery Manager will provide the session deck and recording after each training session. Keep these materials with your onboarding records so your team can revisit the discussion, decisions and demonstrations from your own programme.</p>\n<div class=\"card-grid\">\n  <article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Session deck</h3><p>Use the deck to revisit the topic structure, key decisions and activities covered during the session.</p></article>\n  <article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Session recording</h3><p>Use the recording for catch-up or review, particularly when another team member needs to understand the original discussion.</p></article>\n  <article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Current guidance</h3><p>Check the relevant Hub page and official Marketplacer documentation before repeating a task if the platform or your operating model has changed.</p></article>\n  <article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Your marketplace records</h3><p>Keep any decisions, actions and follow-up questions from the session in your Onboarding Checklist or Decision Register.</p></article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use your own training materials as a point-in-time reference.</strong> The session deck and recording capture the guidance and decisions discussed for your marketplace at that stage of onboarding.</div>\n","Practise with Walkthroughs and Sandbox Activities":"\n<p>Use a walkthrough to understand the screen and task, then complete the activity in Sandbox with representative data. Review the resulting Product, Order, Seller Invoice, Shipment, refund or financial record rather than only the clicks shown in the video.</p>\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n  <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Hands-on practice</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n  <h3>Sandbox Activity Workbook</h3>\n  <p>Complete guided activities across configuration, Seller setup, catalogue, Orders, fulfilment, refunds and Finance.</p>\n  <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Relevant functional team</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Hands-on practice</dd></div></dl>\n  <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/training/activities/sandbox-activity-workbook.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=production-sandbox\">Open guidance</a></div>\n</article></div>\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Platform and configuration</h3><p>Create a restricted user, verify permissions, review Site Details, test an email and compare environment values.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Seller and catalogue</h3><p>Create a test Seller, ingest Products, complete Mapping, correct a Catalog Rule failure and review Product Vetting.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Orders and fulfilment</h3><p>Place a test Order, locate Seller Invoices, complete full and partial fulfilment and return tracking.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Refunds and Finance</h3><p>Complete cancellation or return scenarios and reconcile Marketplacer, payment, commission or wholesale outcomes.</p></article></div>\n<h3>Platform walkthrough library</h3>\n<p>Use these short walkthroughs for task-specific review. The Operator Portal videos support your marketplace team. The Seller Portal videos can also help your team understand the Seller experience and prepare Seller enablement.</p>\n<div class=\"walkthrough-groups\">\n  <details class=\"walkthrough-group\" open><summary><span>Operator Portal walkthroughs</span><small>15 resources</small></summary><div class=\"walkthrough-links\"><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/09026785de194119a1fbe3ce00474144?sid=cc6ef429-77dc-494b-b5ae-14b5e29da774\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Logging into Marketplacer</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/0bbe87bd00944e008c0752df67cd8c3c?sid=23b3d5cc-3d7c-42b8-89fc-2128056c3e09\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Creating a new team member</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/c29e4c30e10345408b29021f8df36ad9?sid=ea87d697-e44d-40ed-9724-752175289816\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Creating user roles</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/1efa12948ca44a9e98aceabfa4c7b6a5?sid=715884d8-476d-4192-9f56-7082d3f4c77f\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Seller Performance Dashboard</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/eef7f67fb60c402e9d9233034e741c6e?sid=4ca5c097-b218-40fd-9d8e-c2e06744507b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Chat</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/20517893578509-Seller-Community-in-the-Operator-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Seller Community</span><strong>Open article</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/36a69e007d884d03b2e85a3b79393c93?sid=66370e37-af11-41b1-a345-81a9b07840d3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Site Details</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/f3f9756e3c2246939072e1a483ad831c?sid=d4388905-cf67-4ce3-8480-29e35284e503\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Account Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/2923ca928e934b099b036e5dbb865489?sid=e9604da3-c6c7-4088-88a7-7f0a8949f6de\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Advert Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/956f1c5c4df346aa95f4cc9d25a16eb2?sid=3fbe255d-49fd-4f7d-aa15-586564cf576a\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Seller Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/df232af1a8d046a58f8138405a1f197e?sid=6cd641ad-69f3-415e-8d21-55c487e27b25\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Finance Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/bd2be03eb701401997e196b3c40fc266?sid=39589984-809e-4707-9dce-fff5a4b253e2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Payment Methods</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/e83cce2409f34e24b536186d98ff1b42?sid=d791bf85-ba77-42f8-a39c-81cbf59d5716\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Reporting tab</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/7f71cf29246c4000b521354ada9c8d89?sid=f8edc648-d4ac-41a0-adce-3ebc1d8a9d24\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>All Sales Report</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/7b2be45821d34559bfbf8a88250bc642?sid=6dcf2096-61a1-400e-a7b4-8066c0438833\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Returns & Refunds Report</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div></details>\n  <details class=\"walkthrough-group\"><summary><span>Seller Portal walkthroughs</span><small>15 resources</small></summary><div class=\"walkthrough-links\"><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/c50cb388a0de434cb2937551ce7935eb?sid=3db7db0c-dc5b-4433-a937-764f7eee5795\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Intro to the Seller Portal</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/c1e4cc28dcdc414c9cf2e107563dc4cf?sid=262b7fe2-ad69-4cb9-b6fa-feb0b300ce0b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Logging into the Seller Portal</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/4fca4444d99c4d94b6900036b69f26b5?sid=4981c532-ccf5-4a66-aed4-0f3a1d5341b0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Left-hand menu walkthrough</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/d59900dadba949fabb87275f5a549350?sid=8bcf922d-8bae-4407-a0f8-cc66feafcb96\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Creating multiple users</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/a9ce63d98bd04523b7bf0029f705c063?sid=e8799e8e-5257-414a-b976-e72a07717a76\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Account Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/705744fb850341bdb769f19a4b6b7b6f?sid=27230c94-57d8-4ba8-be79-cc6c43935c8d\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Business Page Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/a08821a05acc45e2a0220d60de63df26?sid=37f48c5f-a4c2-41b2-a79f-a0005b35c0c6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Store Information</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/e34ec2dc36ef4c359b9c65be231e2e44?sid=09223cd6-0d0c-4a20-a8d1-2bb8415e554b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>User Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/c8915a48f8be472dbce4455e3427d250?sid=8131a69b-49da-42f2-a294-63f0fc4a2c5d\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Commission Packages</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/979e4841c45847aaa49a11a3be383178?sid=26d13a3a-57a8-49f0-bf8e-204049292f16\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Insights & Statistics</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/58db2c1248b54510ad63cdbf32dc270d?sid=dbf9b792-a0e2-40db-bae1-171ad5b6faba\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Change Logs</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/6d8f8c757f5848dcbe069a5b8b1b04a5?sid=5cf53558-cf40-4855-af36-a3bcc850b9a8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Insights & Statistics on Remittances</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/5fbcd22a645948219db1720149f9a0fe?sid=d9bb51fa-bcbe-4d28-99a2-b0f0518d146e\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Sales Summary</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/d7d834ffa92e410fbdcfe4e987ff8b1d?sid=d2d0192d-d9ef-4375-bca3-fbd6c2c56f59\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Understanding Imports & Exports</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/cf388ba203304a55bf9f96a15c8c3034?sid=d24ed9c7-614c-49f5-bc96-342080c16030\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Extensions</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div></details>\n</div>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use the current platform as the source of truth.</strong> A walkthrough may show an earlier navigation label or screen. Confirm current behaviour in the relevant Hub page or Help Center article before changing Production.</div>\n","Use Topic Summaries and Quick Refreshers":"\n<p>Use short refreshers for repeat operational tasks. A refresher should provide the decision, workflow, common errors and link to the complete guidance rather than repeat the whole page.</p>\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operational refresher</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Topic Refresher Template</h3>\n      <p>Create a one-page workflow, decision summary, common-errors guide, field reference or troubleshooting tree.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Relevant process owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Operational refresher</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/training/refreshers/topic-refresher-template.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=marketplacer-resources\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Recommended refresher</th><th>Useful content</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Workflow reference</td><td>Trigger, steps, expected result and escalation</td></tr><tr><td>Decision summary</td><td>Approved position, affected teams and review date</td></tr><tr><td>Common errors</td><td>Symptom, likely cause, evidence and correction</td></tr><tr><td>Field reference</td><td>Field purpose, source of truth and accepted values</td></tr><tr><td>Monthly Finance reference</td><td>Reports, reconciliation sequence, owners and sign-off</td></tr><tr><td>Launch-day reference</td><td>Checks, contacts, decision authority and containment</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","Maintain Training Records and Team Capability":"\n<p>Record both participation and demonstrated capability. Include backup coverage so marketplace operations do not depend on one person.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Assign</strong><span>Map required learning to each role and named team member.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Learn</strong><span>Attend the session or review the current approved resource.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Practise</strong><span>Complete the relevant Sandbox activity.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Review</strong><span>Correct errors and explain the resulting marketplace record.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Confirm</strong><span>Record competency, follow-up and refresher date.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Maintain</strong><span>Reassess capability when ownership, platform behaviour or process changes.</span></div></div>\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Capability governance</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Training Capability Register</h3>\n      <p>Record team member, role, required topics, attendance, practical activities, competency, backup owner and refresher due date.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Functional managers</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Capability governance</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/training/capability/training-capability-register.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=roles-responsibilities\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n","Keep Training Resources Current":"\n<p>Use the decks and recordings supplied during onboarding as point-in-time references. Before your team repeats a task or updates an internal procedure, compare the material with the current Hub guidance, Help Center, Developer Documentation and Changelog.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Review trigger</th><th>What your team should do</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>A platform screen or field differs from the recording</td><td>Check the current Help Center article and follow the configured platform behaviour.</td></tr><tr><td>Your operating model changes</td><td>Update the relevant Decision Register entry, procedure and team refresher.</td></tr><tr><td>A new integration or API change is planned</td><td>Review current Developer Documentation, API Changes and deprecation guidance.</td></tr><tr><td>A process error or incident occurs</td><td>Update the operational refresher after the correction and recovery steps are confirmed.</td></tr><tr><td>A new team member takes ownership</td><td>Assign the learning path, Sandbox practice and competency review.</td></tr><tr><td>Production Readiness or Go-Live approaches</td><td>Confirm that the resources used for critical launch tasks are current.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n  <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator and Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n  <h3>Marketplacer Help Center</h3><p>Use current task and navigation instructions.</p>\n  <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Help Center</a>\n</article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n  <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n  <h3>Developer Documentation</h3><p>Use current Operator API, Seller API and Webhook documentation.</p>\n  <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Developer Documentation</a>\n</article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n  <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">All teams</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n  <h3>Marketplacer Changelog</h3><p>Review product releases, improvements, fixes and sunsetting notices.</p>\n  <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://changelog.marketplacer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog</a>\n</article></div>\n"},"related":[["training-programme","Training Programme"],["roles-responsibilities","Roles and Responsibilities"],["production-sandbox","Production and Sandbox"],["operator-resources","Operator Resources"],["marketplacer-resources","Marketplacer Resources"]]},"seller-resources":{"summary":"Build and maintain the Seller-facing guides, templates, policies and operational resources required to onboard, launch and support each Seller. Provide a core Seller pack to every Seller, then add modules that match the Seller’s connection, commercial and operational model.","audience":["Seller management","Marketplace Operations","Catalogue","Finance","Customer Service","Technology and integrations","Seller training teams"],"sections":{"Understand the Seller Resource Library":"\n<p>The Seller Resource Library helps the Operator assemble the right onboarding and operating pack for each Seller. Provide the core pack to every Seller, then add only the connection, commercial and operational modules that match the approved Seller model.</p>\n<div class=\"resource-equation\"><span>Core Seller Pack</span><b>+</b><span>Connection module</span><b>+</b><span>Commercial module</span><b>+</b><span>Operational modules</span><b>=</b><span class=\"resource-equation-result\">Seller-specific enablement pack</span></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>The Operator remains the primary marketplace contact.</strong> Seller-facing resources explain responsibilities and current Marketplacer tasks, while Seller-specific agreements, rates, credentials and evidence remain private.</div>\n","Assemble the Core Seller Pack":"<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Core Seller Pack</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Welcome Guide</h3>\n      <p>Introduce the marketplace proposition, onboarding stages, responsibilities, contacts, launch expectations and what happens after launch.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Seller onboarding owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Core Seller Pack</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-welcome-guide.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-lifecycle\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Core Seller Pack</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Setup Checklist</h3>\n      <p>Show the Seller-owned actions required for business information, access, Product method, shipping, returns, training, testing and launch.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Seller onboarding owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Core Seller Pack</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-setup-checklist.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-onboarding-process\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Core Seller Pack</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Responsibilities Guide</h3>\n      <p>Set expectations for Product accuracy, stock, fulfilment, tracking, cancellations, returns, security, monitoring and contact maintenance.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Seller management</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Core Seller Pack</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-responsibilities-guide.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-support-boundaries\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div><p>Provide the core pack early enough for the Seller to understand its obligations before Product ingestion and launch testing begin.</p>","Choose Resources by Seller Operating Model":"\n<p>Select resources according to the Seller’s approved connection and operating model.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller method or model</th><th>Provide</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller Portal</td><td>Portal quick start, Product creation, stock, Orders and fulfilment guidance</td></tr><tr><td>Bulk spreadsheet</td><td>Add New, Manage Product Information, Single Sheet, Multi Sheet and error correction guidance</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect</td><td>Connection, Product selection, field ownership, monitoring and recovery guidance</td></tr><tr><td>Seller API</td><td>Authentication, Product, Order, Shipment, refund and reconciliation guidance</td></tr><tr><td>Custom feed or middleware</td><td>Schema, schedule, field ownership, errors and support responsibilities</td></tr><tr><td>Commission</td><td>Commission basis, fees, Promotions, refunds, remittance and payout guidance</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale</td><td>Wholesale Price, Operator retail control, entitlement, refunds, remittance and payout guidance</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Connection selection</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Technical Discovery Form</h3>\n      <p>Assess platform capability, Product and stock sources, Order delivery, fulfilment, refund integration, technical owner and testing availability.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Technology and Seller management</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Connection selection</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-technical-discovery-form.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=product-ingestion\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n","Provide Account, Access and Security Guidance":"\n<p>Give each Seller only the access and security instructions that apply to its users and integration method. Do not place credentials, API keys or MFA recovery codes in the Seller pack.</p>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Intro to the Seller Portal</h3><p>Orient the Seller around Products, Orders, settings and marketplace tasks.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/10552716610829-Intro-to-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Seller Portal guide</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Account Settings in the Seller Portal</h3><p>Maintain store, business, policy and payment-related information.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/32216806648461-Account-Settings-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Account Settings guide</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Manage Multi-Factor Authentication</h3><p>Set up authenticators, recovery codes and access recovery.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39816929271693-Manage-Multi-Factor-Authentication-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open MFA guide</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technical Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller API Getting Started</h3><p>Create a scoped API key and connect to the current GraphQL Seller API.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/getting_started/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open API setup guide</a>\n    </article></div>\n<ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Remove former users promptly and keep current contact details.</li><li>Use the minimum required role or API scope.</li><li>Store credentials and recovery codes in approved secure systems.</li><li>Confirm the Seller knows the Operator support route for access failures.</li></ul>\n","Provide Product and Catalogue Resources":"\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Product and catalogue</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Product Standards Guide</h3>\n      <p>Define title, description, Brand, Category, images, attributes, Variants, SKU, barcode, price fields, stock, shipping, tax and restricted content.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Catalogue and Seller management</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Product and catalogue</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/catalogue/seller-product-standards-guide.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=catalogue-quality\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Creating Products</h3><p>Create Products and Variants using the current Seller workflow.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/29666843938829-Creating-products\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Product guide</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Support for Sellers</h3><p>Find current Product, catalogue and Seller Portal task guidance.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/categories/8810352350989-Support-for-Sellers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Seller Help Center</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Integrated Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>MConnect</h3><p>Understand supported Product, inventory and Order synchronisation.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360012519092-MConnect-Marketplacer-Integrations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open MConnect guide</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technical Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Current Seller API</h3><p>Use the GraphQL Seller API for new Seller integrations.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Seller API</a>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Mapping</h3><p>Explain why Seller values may require Mapping and that suggested Mappings still require approval.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Catalog Rules</h3><p>Explain how validation failures prevent publication and where the authoritative source must be corrected.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Product Vetting</h3><p>Explain why Products or monitored changes may require approval before they appear online.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Source of truth</h3><p>Make clear whether corrections belong in the Seller source, Marketplacer or another approved system.</p></article></div>\n","Provide Order, Fulfilment and Tracking Resources":"\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Orders and fulfilment</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Order and Fulfilment Guide</h3>\n      <p>Explain Seller Invoices, Order receipt, full and partial fulfilment, tracking, dispatch SLA, duplicate prevention and escalation.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Marketplace Operations</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Orders and fulfilment</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/orders/seller-order-and-fulfilment-guide.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=order-lifecycle\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Search and Find Orders</h3><p>Locate current and historical Seller Orders and their operational status.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8837682695053-Search-and-find-orders-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Order search guide</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Dispatch Orders</h3><p>Complete individual or bulk dispatch and retain outstanding quantities for partial dispatch.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838299197197-Dispatch-orders-from-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open dispatch guide</a>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Match the guide to the connection method.</strong> An integrated Seller should follow the approved source-system workflow, while the Portal guide remains useful for visibility and exception handling.</div>\n","Provide Cancellation, Return and Customer Service Resources":"\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Cancellations and returns</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Cancellation and Returns Guide</h3>\n      <p>Separate pre-dispatch cancellation, post-dispatch return, returnless refund, denied request, payment refund and Seller financial adjustment.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Customer Service and Marketplace Operations</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Cancellations and returns</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/returns/seller-cancellation-and-returns-guide.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=refund-foundations\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Seller must understand</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Pre-dispatch cancellation</td><td>The item has not been sent and must follow the approved cancellation workflow.</td></tr><tr><td>Post-dispatch return</td><td>The item was sent and may need physical return, inspection and disposition.</td></tr><tr><td>Returnless refund</td><td>The approved process does not require the item to be returned.</td></tr><tr><td>Denied request</td><td>The request is declined through the approved policy and communication process.</td></tr><tr><td>Customer payment refund</td><td>The Operator or payment provider completes the customer cash movement.</td></tr><tr><td>Seller adjustment</td><td>Marketplacer updates the Seller’s financial position according to the approved model.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator and Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Enable and Use the Returns Module</h3><p>Understand supported pre-dispatch cancellation and post-dispatch return workflows.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040011851-Enable-and-use-the-returns-module\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Returns guide</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Cancel an Order as a Seller</h3><p>Cancel eligible paid but unsent Orders through the Seller Portal.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/8838370021773-Cancel-an-order-as-a-seller\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open cancellation guide</a>\n    </article></div>\n","Provide Commercial, Remittance and Payout Resources":"\n<p>Provide separate commercial modules. The Seller resource must match the signed agreement and assigned commercial model.</p>\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Commission model</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Commission Guide</h3>\n      <p>Explain Commission Package, commission basis, fees, postage treatment, Promotions, refunds, Remittance Advice and payout timing.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Finance and Seller management</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Commission model</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/commercials/seller-commission-guide.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=commission-packages\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Wholesale model</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Wholesale Guide</h3>\n      <p>Explain Wholesale Price, wholesale promotional price, Operator-controlled customer retail price, Seller entitlement, shipping, refunds, remittance and payout.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Finance and Seller management</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Wholesale model</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/commercials/seller-wholesale-guide.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=wholesale-configuration\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Commercial area</th><th>Commission Seller</th><th>Wholesale Seller</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer-facing price</td><td>Customer selling price under the approved marketplace model</td><td>Operator controls or approves the customer retail price</td></tr><tr><td>Seller entitlement basis</td><td>Sale less commission and applicable adjustments</td><td>Wholesale Price and approved Seller entitlements</td></tr><tr><td>Promotion treatment</td><td>Operator-funded or Seller-funded according to the campaign</td><td>Wholesale promotional price changes Seller cost, not customer Sale price automatically</td></tr><tr><td>Operator result</td><td>Commission and applicable fees</td><td>Retail-to-wholesale margin</td></tr><tr><td>Refund effect</td><td>Commission and Seller entitlement adjusted according to the approved workflow</td><td>Historical wholesale entitlement and refund treatment reconciled</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>View Remittance Advice</h3><p>Review the Seller remittance summary and payment status.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/16409413835277-View-remittance-advice-summary-as-a-seller-original-implementation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open remittance guide</a>\n    </article></div>\n","Provide Launch, Performance and Ongoing Support Resources":"\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller launch</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Launch-Day Guide</h3>\n      <p>Confirm activation scope, launch contacts, first-Order expectations, hypercare cadence, issue reporting and pause process.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Seller launch owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Seller launch</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/launch/seller-launch-day-guide.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-launch-readiness\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller support</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Support and Escalation Guide</h3>\n      <p>Explain which issues go to the Operator, Seller technical team, integration owner or Marketplacer Support after Operator triage.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Seller Support owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Seller support</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/support/seller-support-and-escalation-guide.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-support-boundaries\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller and Operator</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Performance Insights</h3><p>Review available sales and service measures and use Order-level evidence where deeper validation is required.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/36711915681933-Seller-performance-insights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open performance guide</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Chat with Your Operator</h3><p>Use the Seller Portal communication channel for marketplace support without sharing sensitive information.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/24164113815437-Chat-with-your-operator\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open chat guide</a>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Issue</th><th>First contact</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product, policy, Mapping or Product Vetting</td><td>Operator</td></tr><tr><td>Order or customer issue</td><td>Operator</td></tr><tr><td>Seller source-system issue</td><td>Seller technical team</td></tr><tr><td>Integration-partner issue</td><td>Approved integration owner</td></tr><tr><td>Confirmed or suspected Marketplacer platform issue</td><td>Marketplacer Support through the Operator</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","Maintain and Distribute Seller Resources":"\n<p>Copy and customise the Seller pack inside the approved Seller workspace. Record which version was supplied, who received it and what practical readiness evidence followed.</p>\n<div class=\"resource-library-grid\"><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller data collection</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Information Questionnaire</h3>\n      <p>Collect the information required to create, configure and support the Seller.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Seller onboarding owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Seller data collection</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-information-questionnaire.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-information\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller readiness evidence</span><span class=\"file-badge\">XLSX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Readiness Register</h3>\n      <p>Track account, connection, catalogue, operations, Finance, training and test evidence.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Seller launch owner</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Seller readiness evidence</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-readiness-register.xlsx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-launch-readiness\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article><article class=\"resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller launch decision</span><span class=\"file-badge\">DOCX</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Launch Approval Record</h3>\n      <p>Record final approval, conditions, activation scope and monitoring.</p>\n      <dl class=\"resource-meta\"><div><dt>Primary owner</dt><dd>Launch authority</dd></div><div><dt>Use it for</dt><dd>Seller launch decision</dd></div></dl>\n      \n      <div class=\"resource-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"resources/seller/onboarding/seller-launch-approval-record.docx\" download>Download template</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"?page=seller-launch-readiness\">Open guidance</a></div>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Do not publish publicly</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Signed agreements and commercial schedules</td><td>Commercially confidential</td></tr><tr><td>Bank, tax, KYC or identity information</td><td>Sensitive personal and financial information</td></tr><tr><td>Credentials, API secrets and MFA recovery codes</td><td>Security risk</td></tr><tr><td>Private Seller contacts and incident records</td><td>Operational confidentiality</td></tr><tr><td>Customer-specific recordings and Production exports</td><td>May contain restricted data and marketplace-specific context</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n"},"related":[["seller-lifecycle","Seller Lifecycle"],["seller-information","Seller Information to Collect"],["seller-onboarding-process","Seller Onboarding Process"],["seller-support-boundaries","Seller Support Boundaries"],["seller-launch-readiness","Seller Launch Readiness"],["getting-support","Getting Support"]]},"marketplacer-resources":{"summary":"Use Marketplacer’s trusted documentation, technical references, release updates, platform-health information and marketplace strategy resources. Choose the source that matches your question and confirm that it applies to your environment and operating model.","audience":["All Operator teams","Seller enablement teams","Technology and integrations","Marketplace leadership"],"sections":{"Understand the Marketplacer Resource Ecosystem":"\n<p>Use the source that matches the question. The Hub provides end-to-end Operator context, while official Marketplacer resources provide current task, technical, release, status and strategy information.</p>\n<div class=\"source-map\">\n  <article><span>How should our marketplace operate?</span><strong>Operator Onboarding Hub</strong><p>Operating model, responsibilities, sequence and governance.</p></article>\n  <article><span>How do I complete a platform task?</span><strong>Marketplacer Help Center</strong><p>Current Operator and Seller procedures.</p></article>\n  <article><span>How does an integration behave?</span><strong>Developer Documentation</strong><p>APIs, Webhooks, errors, retries and technical contracts.</p></article>\n  <article><span>What has changed?</span><strong>Changelog and API Changes</strong><p>Releases, fixes, sunsetting and migration context.</p></article>\n  <article><span>Is a service currently affected?</span><strong>Marketplacer Status</strong><p>Check current incidents, maintenance and component health.</p><a class=\"source-map-link\" href=\"https://status.marketplacer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Marketplacer Status</a></article>\n  <article><span>How do marketplaces grow?</span><strong>Resource Hub and Case Studies</strong><p>Strategy, examples and broader marketplace learning.</p></article>\n  <article><span>The documentation did not resolve it</span><strong>Getting Support</strong><p>Triage, evidence and escalation.</p></article>\n</div>\n","Choose the Right Source":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Question</th><th>Start with</th><th>Why</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>How should our marketplace operate?</td><td>Operator Onboarding Hub</td><td>Provides operating context and approved marketplace guidance.</td></tr><tr><td>Where is a setting located?</td><td>Marketplacer Help Center</td><td>Provides current task and navigation instructions.</td></tr><tr><td>How should a Seller complete a Portal task?</td><td>Support for Sellers</td><td>Provides Seller-specific procedures.</td></tr><tr><td>What fields, queries or mutations are available?</td><td>Developer Documentation</td><td>Defines current technical contracts and examples.</td></tr><tr><td>How do Webhook retries behave?</td><td>Developer Documentation</td><td>Defines delivery, failure and retry behaviour.</td></tr><tr><td>Was a feature changed or released?</td><td>Marketplacer Changelog</td><td>Provides product release and update history.</td></tr><tr><td>Is an API changing or being deprecated?</td><td>API Changes and Deprecation Process</td><td>Supports technical migration planning.</td></tr><tr><td>Is a platform service degraded?</td><td>Marketplacer Status</td><td>Provides current operational status.</td></tr><tr><td>How have other businesses used marketplaces?</td><td>Resource Hub and Case Studies</td><td>Provides strategic examples.</td></tr><tr><td>Documentation does not resolve the issue</td><td>Getting Support</td><td>Provides the escalation and evidence process.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Confirm applicability.</strong> Check the audience, environment, feature configuration, connector, commercial model and publication date before applying guidance.</div>","Use the Marketplacer Help Center":"\n<p>Use the Help Center for current Operator Portal and Seller Portal procedures, configuration steps, Product and Order workflows, Finance processes, integration setup, troubleshooting and submitting a request.</p>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator and Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplacer Help Center</h3><p>Browse current task guidance by Products, Orders, Finance, integrations, shipping, administration, security and troubleshooting.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Help Center</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Support for Sellers</h3><p>Use Seller-specific Portal, Product, Order and operational guidance.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/categories/8810352350989-Support-for-Sellers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Seller Support</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">All teams</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplacer Glossary</h3><p>Confirm current Marketplacer terminology before interpreting an article or technical field.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4414397900941-Marketplacer-glossary\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Glossary</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Submit a Request</h3><p>Contact Marketplacer Support after triage and evidence collection.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/requests/new\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open request form</a>\n    </article></div>\n<ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Confirm whether the article is for an Operator or Seller.</li><li>Confirm whether it applies to the Operator Portal, Seller Portal or an integration tool.</li><li>Confirm the feature is enabled for the marketplace.</li><li>Check whether the article describes a current or original implementation.</li><li>Check the article date against the training recording or internal procedure.</li></ul>\n","Use Developer Documentation":"\n<p>Use the Developer Portal for Operator API, current Seller API, Webhooks, authentication, pagination, errors, retries, deduplication, high-volume patterns, API changes and deprecations.</p>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Developer Documentation</h3><p>Start with the current Marketplacer technical documentation.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Developer Documentation</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Operator API</h3><p>Build Operator-controlled integrations across Product, Order, taxonomy and refund workflows.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/operator-api/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Operator API</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller API</h3><p>Use the current GraphQL Seller API for new Seller integrations.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/seller-api/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Seller API</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Webhooks Overview</h3><p>Understand event-driven integration design and operational responsibilities.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/webhooksoverview/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Webhooks guide</a>\n    </article></div>\n<h3>Read technical documentation safely</h3>\n<ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Confirm Operator API or Seller API.</li><li>Confirm current GraphQL API or legacy API.</li><li>Confirm Sandbox or Production endpoint and authentication method.</li><li>Use the minimum required permissions and scopes.</li><li>Plan pagination, volume, External IDs, retries, duplicate prevention and error handling.</li><li>Review relevant API changes and deprecations before development or major testing.</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not start new work on the legacy Seller API.</strong> Use the current GraphQL Seller API unless an approved existing implementation requires legacy maintenance.</div>\n","Track Product, API and Integration Changes":"\n<p>Review release information before major testing, Production Readiness, Go-Live and material integration changes.</p>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">All teams</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplacer Changelog</h3><p>Review product releases, improvements, fixes and sunsetting notices.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://changelog.marketplacer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>API Changes</h3><p>Review API and Webhook changes, documentation updates and deprecation guidance.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/changes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review API Changes</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Webhook Retry Policy</h3><p>Confirm current retry and failure behaviour.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/webhookretries/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Retry Policy</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Webhook Deduplication</h3><p>Understand standard and optional deduplication behaviour.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/deduplication/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Deduplication guide</a>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Review the change</strong><span>Understand the release, fix, deprecation or documentation update.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Confirm applicability</strong><span>Identify affected features, environments, Sellers and integrations.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Assess impact</strong><span>Record required configuration, code, testing, communication or documentation changes.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Implement and test</strong><span>Apply through the approved change process and retain evidence.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Communicate</strong><span>Update affected teams, Sellers and support procedures.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Close</strong><span>Record completion, residual risk and next review date.</span></div></div>\n","Monitor Platform Health and Service Issues":"\n<div class=\"status-resource-card\">\n  <div><span class=\"resource-tag\">Live platform information</span><h3>Marketplacer Status</h3><p>Check current component health, active incidents, scheduled maintenance and recent service history when a broad or unusual issue may affect several users, Sellers, integrations or workflows.</p></div>\n  <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://status.marketplacer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Marketplacer Status</a>\n</div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Check Marketplacer Status when</th><th>Continue to retain</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Operator Portal or Seller Portal access is broadly affected</td><td>Affected users, timestamps and business impact</td></tr><tr><td>Several API requests or integrations fail together</td><td>Request IDs, endpoints, errors and retries</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect behaviour changes across several Sellers</td><td>Seller and task references, last successful activity and source-system evidence</td></tr><tr><td>Email delivery appears delayed across the marketplace</td><td>Mail logs, recipients, timestamps and message type</td></tr><tr><td>A reported incident may explain the symptom</td><td>Order, payment, refund and Finance reconciliation records</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Status information does not replace reconciliation.</strong> Protect open Orders, customer communication, Seller operations and financial records while the service issue is investigated. Submit a Support request where investigation or reconciliation is still required.</div>\n","Use Seller Community and Platform Ecosystem Resources":"\n<p>Use ecosystem resources to support Seller discovery, connection options and marketplace growth. Continue to apply the Operator’s Seller qualification, commercial review, technical discovery, onboarding and readiness controls.</p>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller growth</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplacer Seller Community</h3><p>Explore marketplace and Seller connection opportunities.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://community.marketplacer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Seller Community</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technology and marketplace teams</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplacer Partners</h3><p>Review the wider partner and connector ecosystem.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://marketplacer.com/partners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Explore Partners</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller enablement</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Support for Sellers</h3><p>Direct Sellers to current task-specific support after the Operator has set marketplace expectations.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/categories/8810352350989-Support-for-Sellers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Seller Support</a>\n    </article></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Discovery does not equal approval.</strong> Every Seller still requires commercial, range, technical, catalogue and launch-readiness review.</div>\n","Explore Marketplace Strategy and Success Resources":"\n<p>Use strategic resources for business cases, Seller propositions, range expansion, stakeholder education, category planning and marketplace maturity. Treat case studies as examples, not configuration instructions.</p>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Leadership and strategy</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplacer Resource Hub</h3><p>Explore articles, guides, webinars, reports and broader marketplace learning.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://marketplacer.com/resource-hub/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Resource Hub</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Leadership and strategy</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplace Case Studies</h3><p>Review examples of marketplace outcomes and operating approaches.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://marketplacer.com/case-studies/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Explore Case Studies</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator leadership</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Operator Case Studies</h3><p>Review examples from organisations operating Marketplacer marketplaces.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://marketplacer.com/case-studies/operator-case-studies/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Explore Operator Stories</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Seller strategy</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Seller Case Studies</h3><p>Review Seller participation and marketplace-growth examples.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://marketplacer.com/case-studies/seller-case-studies/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Explore Seller Stories</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Security and technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Technology and Security</h3><p>Review Marketplacer’s published technology and security information.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://marketplacer.com/security/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Security information</a>\n    </article></div>\n","Maintain a Trusted Resource Directory":"\n<p>Curate a small, reliable directory rather than copying large amounts of external content into the Hub.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Metadata</th><th>Record</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Resource name and type</td><td>Help Center, Developer, Changelog, Status, community or strategy</td></tr><tr><td>Intended audience</td><td>Operator, Seller, technology, Finance, leadership or Customer Service</td></tr><tr><td>Use it for</td><td>The question or task it resolves</td></tr><tr><td>Authority</td><td>Current official Marketplacer source or internal approved guidance</td></tr><tr><td>Status</td><td>Current, conditional or legacy</td></tr><tr><td>Related Hub page</td><td>The operating context and responsibilities</td></tr><tr><td>Last reviewed</td><td>Date the link and applicability were confirmed</td></tr><tr><td>Review trigger</td><td>Content sprint, release, incident, integration change or scheduled review</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Resource area</th><th>Suggested review trigger</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Help Center links</td><td>When the related Hub page is revised</td></tr><tr><td>Developer links</td><td>Before integration development or major testing</td></tr><tr><td>Changelog</td><td>Regularly and before Production changes</td></tr><tr><td>API deprecations</td><td>During technical planning and maintenance</td></tr><tr><td>Platform Status</td><td>During active incidents</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Community</td><td>During Seller acquisition and range expansion</td></tr><tr><td>Resource Hub and case studies</td><td>During strategy and capability planning</td></tr><tr><td>Public Hub links</td><td>During every content sprint</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n"},"related":[["operator-resources","Operator Resources"],["training-resources","Training Resources"],["seller-resources","Seller Resources"],["integration-architecture","Integration Architecture"],["getting-support","Getting Support"]]},"marketplacer-services":{"summary":"Explore additional Marketplacer expertise and execution capacity when your team needs help with architecture, integrations, developer enablement, feature adoption, analytics, Seller onboarding, Product data or ongoing Seller operations. These services supplement your contracted onboarding, Customer Success and Support arrangements.","audience":["Marketplace leadership","Technology and integrations","Seller management","Catalogue","Marketplace Operations","Customer Success stakeholders"],"sections":{"Understand Marketplacer Services":"\n<p>Your team remains responsible for the marketplace strategy, decisions and operating model, but you do not need to solve every specialist or capacity challenge alone. Marketplacer offers additional services that can supplement your team when a workstream requires deeper expertise, dedicated delivery capacity or ongoing operational support.</p>\n<div class=\"service-model-grid\">\n  <article class=\"service-model-card expert-services\">\n    <span class=\"service-model-tag\">Project-based expertise</span>\n    <h3>Expert Services</h3>\n    <p>Specialist strategic and technical support for a defined problem, project or outcome.</p>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Architecture and integration guidance</li><li>Developer enablement and API support</li><li>Feature adoption and marketplace strategy</li><li>Analytics, reporting and delivery collaboration</li></ul>\n  </article>\n  <article class=\"service-model-card srm-services\">\n    <span class=\"service-model-tag\">Ongoing managed capacity</span>\n    <h3>Seller Relationship Management</h3>\n    <p>Recurring execution support across the Seller lifecycle and Product onboarding operation.</p>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Seller readiness and onboarding</li><li>Product data ingestion and validation</li><li>Seller performance and first-line support</li><li>Seller recruitment where separately included</li></ul>\n  </article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Additional services extend your team.</strong> Your marketplace retains control over strategy, Seller selection, commercial terms, Product approval and marketplace policies. The agreed service provides specialist expertise or execution capacity around those decisions.</div>\n","Separate Standard Support from Additional Services":"\n<p>Marketplacer Services do not replace your contracted onboarding, Customer Success or Support arrangements. They are separately scoped when your team needs work beyond the standard service included in your agreement.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Source of help</th><th>Use it for</th><th>What it does not replace</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Operator Onboarding Hub and documentation</td><td>Self-service guidance, operating context and current platform procedures</td><td>Marketplace decisions, specialist delivery work or incident investigation</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Standard onboarding and Customer Success</td><td>The activities, reviews and enablement included in your agreement</td><td>Custom projects or ongoing managed operational capacity</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Marketplacer Support</td><td>Platform questions, suspected defects, incidents and technical investigation</td><td>Project delivery, custom architecture, Seller recruitment or ongoing Seller operations</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Additional Marketplacer Services</td><td>Separately scoped strategic, technical or managed operational work</td><td>Your team’s decision authority and responsibilities under the marketplace operating model</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Your agreement is the authority.</strong> Standard inclusions vary by contract and pricing plan. Confirm the proposed scope with your Marketplacer Customer Success Manager, Delivery Manager or account contact before relying on a service.</div>\n","Choose the Right Service Model":"\n<p>Start with the type of help you need, the duration of the work and the ownership gap your team is trying to solve.</p>\n<div class=\"service-choice-grid\">\n  <article><span>Defined project</span><h3>Choose Expert Services</h3><p>You need specialist input for a specific technical, strategic, analytical or adoption outcome.</p><strong>Examples</strong><p>Architecture review, integration design, developer workshop, custom reporting or feature-adoption support.</p></article>\n  <article><span>Recurring Seller workload</span><h3>Choose SRM</h3><p>You need ongoing capacity to execute repeatable Seller and Product operations month after month.</p><strong>Examples</strong><p>Seller onboarding, Product data processing, listing quality, performance monitoring or first-line Seller support.</p></article>\n  <article><span>Mixed or unclear need</span><h3>Discuss the operating problem first</h3><p>Describe the outcome, constraints and current ownership gap. Marketplacer can help determine whether a project, managed service or internal action is the best fit.</p></article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Your need</th><th>Likely starting point</th><th>Why</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Validate a connected-commerce architecture</td><td>Expert Services</td><td>Requires specialist technical review and recommendations.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Help developers work with APIs and Webhooks</td><td>Expert Services</td><td>Requires focused enablement or problem-solving.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Adopt a new platform capability</td><td>Expert Services</td><td>Requires a defined workshop, operating assessment or implementation plan.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Onboard a growing Seller pipeline</td><td>SRM</td><td>Requires recurring coordination and execution capacity.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Process and validate large volumes of Seller Product data</td><td>SRM</td><td>Requires repeatable operational work across ingestion, Mapping and listing quality.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Recruit and progress new Sellers</td><td>SRM where included</td><td>Requires an agreed outreach and pipeline-conversion scope.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n","Use Expert Services for Specialist Projects":"\n<p>Expert Services are most useful when the desired outcome is defined, but your team needs Marketplacer-specific strategic or technical expertise to reach it efficiently.</p>\n<div class=\"service-capability-grid\">\n  <article><span>Architecture and integration</span><h3>Design the connected solution</h3><p>Integration consulting, composable commerce strategy and architecture reviews across Marketplacer and your ecommerce, ERP, OMS, PIM, CRM or other connected systems.</p></article>\n  <article><span>Developers and delivery partners</span><h3>Enable implementation teams</h3><p>Developer enablement and advocacy for teams using Marketplacer APIs, Webhooks and integration patterns, including support for specific technical challenges.</p></article>\n  <article><span>Capability adoption</span><h3>Turn features into operating outcomes</h3><p>Feature-adoption workshops that connect a Marketplacer capability to your business process, ownership model, configuration and rollout plan.</p></article>\n  <article><span>Data and decisions</span><h3>Extend reporting and insight</h3><p>Analytics and BI assistance for custom queries, reports or dashboards where standard reporting does not answer the business question.</p></article>\n  <article><span>Marketplace strategy</span><h3>Prioritise growth and improvement</h3><p>Strategic guidance to assess marketplace opportunities, sequence work and focus leadership attention on the highest-value outcomes.</p></article>\n  <article><span>Project collaboration</span><h3>Add specialist participation</h3><p>Agreed participation in work-in-progress sessions, technical reviews or delivery forums where Marketplacer expertise is needed to progress decisions and implementation.</p></article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Define the outcome before the activity.</strong> “We need architecture help” becomes more actionable when the brief identifies the systems, decision, risk, target state and milestone that the review must support.</div>\n","Use Seller Relationship Management for Ongoing Capacity":"\n<p>Seller Relationship Management, or SRM, is designed for Operators that need repeatable Seller-operational capacity rather than a single project. The exact scope is agreed with Marketplacer and can vary with Seller volume, connection complexity and marketplace maturity.</p>\n<div class=\"srm-pillar-grid\">\n  <article><span>01</span><h3>Seller readiness and onboarding</h3><p>Seller account setup, access, onboarding guidance, platform orientation and support preparing the first Product submission.</p></article>\n  <article><span>02</span><h3>Product data ingestion and quality</h3><p>Product data processing, taxonomy Mapping, validation, listing quality review and remediation coordination before Operator approval.</p></article>\n  <article><span>03</span><h3>Performance and Seller support</h3><p>Light-touch operational compliance review, performance monitoring, documented recommendations and first-line help for routine platform or fulfilment questions.</p></article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"service-optional-panel\"><div><span>Conditional service</span><h3>Seller growth and recruitment</h3><p>Where included in the agreed scope, Marketplacer may support Seller identification, outreach, pipeline progression and conversion preparation. Your team retains final control over commercial terms, Seller approval and contract execution.</p></div></div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Your team retains</th><th>The agreed SRM service can support</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Seller strategy and target profile</td><td>Execution against the agreed onboarding or outreach plan</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Commercial terms and final agreements</td><td>Seller education, coordination and pipeline progression where scoped</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Taxonomy, Product standards and marketplace policies</td><td>Mapping, validation and identification of Product data gaps</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Final Product and Seller launch approval</td><td>Readiness preparation, evidence and remediation follow-up</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Performance standards and enforcement decisions</td><td>Monitoring, first-line support and documented recommendations</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n","Recognise When Additional Services Could Help":"\n<p>Consider a services conversation when the issue is not a lack of documentation, but a genuine expertise, capacity or delivery gap.</p>\n<div class=\"service-signal-grid\">\n  <article><strong>Capacity pressure</strong><p>Seller onboarding, Product processing or operational queues are growing faster than the internal team can manage.</p></article>\n  <article><strong>Specialist technical risk</strong><p>The marketplace architecture, integration or API design requires Marketplacer-specific expertise.</p></article>\n  <article><strong>Time-to-market pressure</strong><p>A launch, feature or Seller cohort needs focused capacity to avoid becoming a programme bottleneck.</p></article>\n  <article><strong>Persistent Product data issues</strong><p>Mapping, validation, listing quality or remediation work is delaying Seller activation and catalogue expansion.</p></article>\n  <article><strong>Capability adoption gap</strong><p>Your team owns a Marketplacer feature but lacks a clear operating model or implementation approach.</p></article>\n  <article><strong>Reporting gap</strong><p>Standard reporting does not provide the analysis or operational view required for a business decision.</p></article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Do not purchase capacity for an undefined problem.</strong> First identify the outcome, current owner, bottleneck, affected scope and expected measure of success. This creates a stronger service brief and a clearer internal business case.</div>\n","Prepare for a Services Conversation":"\n<p>Provide enough context for Marketplacer to understand the operating problem and propose an appropriate scope.</p>\n<div class=\"service-brief-grid\">\n  <article><span>01</span><strong>Outcome</strong><p>What must be different when the engagement is complete?</p></article>\n  <article><span>02</span><strong>Current state</strong><p>What process, system or team exists today, and where is the gap?</p></article>\n  <article><span>03</span><strong>Scope</strong><p>Which Sellers, Products, integrations, teams, environments or regions are involved?</p></article>\n  <article><span>04</span><strong>Timing</strong><p>Which milestone or business deadline is driving the request?</p></article>\n  <article><span>05</span><strong>Ownership</strong><p>Who will make decisions, provide inputs, approve outputs and own the result?</p></article>\n  <article><span>06</span><strong>Constraints</strong><p>What technical, commercial, security, data or resourcing constraints must be considered?</p></article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"copy-template compact\"><div class=\"copy-template-heading\"><strong>Services discussion brief</strong><span>Prepare before the conversation</span></div><pre>Business outcome:\nCurrent challenge:\nWhy the current team or process cannot resolve it alone:\nAffected Sellers, Products, systems or teams:\nTarget milestone:\nCurrent owner and decision-maker:\nKnown constraints and dependencies:\nEvidence, examples or current metrics:\nPreferred working model: project-based, ongoing or to be assessed</pre></div>\n","Confirm Scope, Ownership and Commercials":"\n<p>Before work begins, confirm the boundary between your team and the agreed Marketplacer service. The scope should be specific enough to manage effort, decisions, dependencies and acceptance.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Confirm</th><th>Questions to answer</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Outcome and deliverables</td><td>What will be produced, completed, reviewed or handed over?</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Inclusions and exclusions</td><td>Which work is in scope, and which responsibilities remain with the Operator or another partner?</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Participants and authority</td><td>Who provides inputs, makes decisions, approves outputs and resolves blockers?</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Data and access</td><td>Which environments, systems and records are required, and how will access be controlled?</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Dependencies</td><td>Which Seller, agency, integration-partner or internal activities must happen first?</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Cadence and reporting</td><td>How will progress, risks, consumed capacity and decisions be communicated?</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Commercial arrangement</td><td>What charging model, duration and service capacity are agreed?</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Completion and handover</td><td>How will the outcome be accepted, documented and transitioned to your team?</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not rely on this public page as a statement of contractual inclusions.</strong> Service names, availability, scope and commercials must be confirmed in the applicable proposal, order form or agreement.</div>\n","Discuss Services with Your Marketplacer Team":"\n<div class=\"services-contact-panel\">\n  <div>\n    <span>Start the conversation</span>\n    <h3>Bring the operating problem, not just a service name.</h3>\n    <p>During onboarding, speak with your Marketplacer Delivery Manager. After onboarding, speak with your Customer Success Manager or account contact. They can help assess the need, confirm current availability and coordinate the appropriate services conversation.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"service-contact-routes\">\n  <article><h3>During onboarding</h3><p>Discuss the gap with your Delivery Manager so it can be assessed alongside the implementation plan, dependencies and launch scope.</p></article>\n  <article><h3>After onboarding</h3><p>Discuss the opportunity with your Customer Success Manager or account contact as part of marketplace planning and prioritisation.</p></article>\n  <article><h3>Platform incident or defect</h3><p>Use the Getting Support guidance instead. Support requests and paid services solve different types of need.</p></article>\n</div>\n"},"related":[["operator-resources","Operator Resources"],["seller-onboarding-process","Seller Onboarding Process"],["seller-performance","Seller Performance"],["integration-architecture","Integration Architecture"],["marketplacer-resources","Marketplacer Resources"],["getting-support","Getting Support"]]},"getting-support":{"summary":"Triage marketplace questions and incidents, identify the responsible system or team, collect complete evidence and use the correct Marketplacer Support route when self-service guidance and Operator investigation do not resolve the issue.","audience":["Marketplace Operations","Customer Service","Seller Support","Technology and integrations","Finance","Incident managers","Operator administrators"],"sections":{"Understand the Support Operating Model":"\n<p>The Operator owns the marketplace relationship and completes first-line triage. Marketplacer Support assists the Operator with Marketplacer platform questions and issues after documentation, configuration, source data and connected-system evidence have been reviewed.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Customer or Seller raises an issue</strong><span>The Operator records the affected journey, record and business impact.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Operator completes first-line triage</strong><span>Confirm the environment, user, Seller, Product, Order or integration scope.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Identify the responsible boundary</strong><span>Determine whether the correction belongs in Marketplacer, the storefront, Seller source, payment provider or another system.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Resolve or contain</strong><span>Apply an owned correction or the smallest effective containment action.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Escalate when required</strong><span>Submit complete evidence for confirmed or suspected Marketplacer behaviour.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Reconcile and communicate</strong><span>Protect customers, Sellers and financial records until resolution.</span></div></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Submitting a request does not transfer operational ownership.</strong> Continue containment, evidence collection, reconciliation and stakeholder communication while investigation is active.</div>\n","Know Who Supports Whom":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Person raising the issue</th><th>First support route</th><th>Escalation route</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer</td><td>Operator Customer Service</td><td>Operator Operations, Finance or technology teams</td></tr><tr><td>Seller</td><td>Operator Seller Support or Seller Manager</td><td>Operator technology team, then Marketplacer Support where required</td></tr><tr><td>Operator user</td><td>Operator internal support owner</td><td>Marketplacer Support</td></tr><tr><td>Integration partner</td><td>Operator technical owner</td><td>Marketplacer Support for confirmed Marketplacer behaviour</td></tr><tr><td>Payment-provider issue</td><td>Operator Payments or Finance team</td><td>Payment provider, or Marketplacer Support where the Marketplacer integration is involved</td></tr><tr><td>MPay issue</td><td>Operator</td><td>Marketplacer Support</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer platform issue</td><td>Operator</td><td>Marketplacer Support</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Keep one marketplace support route.</strong> Sellers should not bypass the Operator for routine marketplace questions, Product governance, Orders or operating-policy decisions.</div>","Classify the Question or Issue":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Issue type</th><th>Example</th><th>Likely first action</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>How-to question</td><td>Where a setting is located</td><td>Review the Hub and Help Center</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplace decision</td><td>Whether Sellers may initiate cancellations</td><td>Review the approved operating model</td></tr><tr><td>Configuration issue</td><td>Wrong Seller default or notification address</td><td>Review configuration and Seller overrides</td></tr><tr><td>Access issue</td><td>User cannot access an expected area</td><td>Review user, role, MFA and SSO configuration</td></tr><tr><td>Seller data issue</td><td>Incorrect price, stock or Product content</td><td>Check the Seller source and ingestion workflow</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue issue</td><td>Product offline due to Mapping or Catalog Rules</td><td>Review Product status and validation evidence</td></tr><tr><td>Integration issue</td><td>Webhook, API or MConnect event failed</td><td>Review logs, payloads, responses and retries</td></tr><tr><td>Payment or Finance issue</td><td>Payment and Order do not reconcile</td><td>Review payment, Order, refund and remittance records</td></tr><tr><td>Suspected defect</td><td>Repeatable result differs from expected platform behaviour</td><td>Collect reproduction evidence and report a bug</td></tr><tr><td>Service incident</td><td>Several users or workflows fail together</td><td>Check Platform Status and activate incident response</td></tr><tr><td>Feature request</td><td>The desired workflow is not currently available</td><td>Submit a platform suggestion or discuss with the Marketplacer team</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Check Documentation and Current Platform Information":"\n<p>Use the source that matches the question. For a critical live incident, documentation review, containment and Support escalation may run in parallel.</p>\n<div class=\"resource-journey\"><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>1</span><strong>Hub</strong><p>Confirm the expected operating model and responsible owner</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>2</span><strong>Help Center</strong><p>Confirm the current platform task and known guidance</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>3</span><strong>Developer docs</strong><p>Confirm API, Webhook, error and retry behaviour</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>4</span><strong>Changelog</strong><p>Check recent releases, fixes and sunsetting</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>5</span><strong>Platform Status</strong><p>Check current service health when the impact is broad</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>6</span><strong>Internal evidence</strong><p>Review configuration, source systems, logs and recent changes</p></article><article class=\"resource-stage\"><span>7</span><strong>Marketplacer Support</strong><p>Escalate unresolved Marketplacer questions or issues</p></article></div>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Troubleshooting</h3><p>Review known errors, troubleshooting guidance and escalation preparation.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/categories/360006084971-Troubleshooting\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Troubleshooting</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">All teams</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplacer Changelog</h3><p>Check for relevant product changes and fixes.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://changelog.marketplacer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator and technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Marketplacer Status</h3><p>Check current service-health information.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://status.marketplacer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Platform Status</a>\n    </article></div>\n","Triage and Isolate the Problem":"\n<p>Describe the symptom precisely, then trace the journey to the first failing boundary.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Confirm the symptom</strong><span>Record what the user or system observed without assuming the cause.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Identify the affected record</strong><span>Capture the Product, Variant, Order, Seller Invoice, Shipment, refund or integration reference.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Trace backwards</strong><span>Follow the journey from the visible symptom to the last confirmed successful stage.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Find the failing boundary</strong><span>Identify the first transfer, configuration or processing stage that did not produce the expected result.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Test repeatability</strong><span>Confirm whether the issue is continuous, intermittent or isolated.</span></div><div class=\"process-step process-step-labelled\"><strong>Preserve evidence</strong><span>Capture logs, IDs and timestamps before changing the record.</span></div></div>\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Scope</h3><p>Production or Sandbox, one or several users, one or several Sellers, one record or a pattern.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Timing</h3><p>First observed, last successful occurrence, time zone and recent changes.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Journey</h3><p>Customer-facing, Seller-facing, financial, integration or internal administration.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Ownership</h3><p>Marketplacer, storefront, Seller source, payment provider, middleware or an Operator decision.</p></article></div>\n","Review Available Operational Evidence":"\n<p>Collect the smallest complete evidence set required to understand and reproduce the issue.</p>\n<div class=\"evidence-grid\">\n  <article><h3>Marketplace records</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Seller ID</li><li>Product and Variant IDs</li><li>Marketplacer Order ID</li><li>Seller Invoice ID</li><li>Shipment or refund reference</li><li>Remittance Advice</li><li>External IDs</li></ul></article>\n  <article><h3>Operator Portal evidence</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Problem Reports</li><li>Activity Logs</li><li>Mail Sending Logs</li><li>Imports and Exports</li><li>Order and Product history</li><li>Webhook records</li><li>Payment or remittance reports</li></ul></article>\n  <article><h3>Integration evidence</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Request and response</li><li>Endpoint and operation</li><li>HTTP status or GraphQL errors</li><li>Event or request ID</li><li>Timestamp and retry history</li><li>Seller-system reference</li><li>MConnect task or import error</li></ul></article>\n  <article><h3>User evidence</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Screenshot and page URL</li><li>User role and environment</li><li>Actions completed</li><li>Visible error</li><li>Affected account</li><li>Time observed</li></ul></article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator administrator</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Operator User Role Permissions</h3><p>Confirm support users have only the access required for logs, reports, API keys and Webhooks.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open permissions guide</a>\n    </article></div>\n","Assess Business Impact and Urgency":"\n<p>Use an internal priority to control the Operator response. Do not present this table as a promise of Marketplacer response times. Contractual support terms remain the authority.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Internal priority</th><th>Example impact</th><th>Immediate Operator response</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Critical</td><td>Customers charged without recoverable Orders, duplicate Orders, widespread wrong pricing or serious security exposure</td><td>Contain impact, activate the incident team and escalate immediately</td></tr><tr><td>High</td><td>A launch Seller receives no Orders, fulfilment cannot return or refunds cannot be completed</td><td>Assign an incident owner, apply targeted containment and escalate</td></tr><tr><td>Medium</td><td>A Product range fails publication or one integration workflow is degraded with a workaround</td><td>Investigate, document the workaround and submit complete evidence</td></tr><tr><td>Low</td><td>Minor presentation, content or isolated administration issue</td><td>Record, investigate and submit through the normal route</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul class=\"criteria-list\"><li>Number and type of customers or Sellers affected.</li><li>Financial, privacy, legal or brand impact.</li><li>Whether impact is accumulating.</li><li>Whether a safe workaround exists.</li><li>Whether open Orders, refunds or payouts remain at risk.</li></ul>\n","Choose the Correct Support Request":"\n<p>Use the current Marketplacer request form and select the route that matches the evidence.</p>\n<div class=\"request-card-grid\">\n  <article class=\"request-card\"><span>Question</span><h3>Ask a General Question</h3><p>Use when current documentation does not clarify expected behaviour or capability and no defect has been confirmed.</p></article>\n  <article class=\"request-card\"><span>Defect</span><h3>Report a Bug</h3><p>Use when current behaviour differs from the expected result after configuration, permissions and source data have been checked.</p></article>\n  <article class=\"request-card\"><span>Future capability</span><h3>Platform Suggestions or Considerations</h3><p>Use when the requested workflow or capability is not currently available.</p></article>\n  <article class=\"request-card\"><span>Access</span><h3>Unblock Multi-Factor Authentication</h3><p>Use when an authorised user cannot complete MFA and normal recovery guidance does not resolve access.</p></article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"resource-actions standalone-actions\"><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/requests/new\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open the Support request form</a><a class=\"resource-action secondary\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360003888972-Reporting-a-bug\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Review bug-reporting guidance</a></div>\n","Submit a Complete Support Request":"\n<p>Describe the affected marketplace journey, expected result, actual result and business impact. Include record identifiers and evidence that allow the issue to be investigated without repeated clarification.</p>\n<div class=\"copy-template\"><div class=\"copy-template-heading\"><strong>Support request template</strong><span>Copy into the request form</span></div><pre>Marketplace:\nEnvironment: Production or Sandbox\nBusiness impact:\nAffected users or Sellers:\nAffected records and IDs:\nFirst observed: date, time and time zone\nLast known successful occurrence:\nIssue description:\nSteps to reproduce:\nExpected result:\nActual result:\nFrequency: always, intermittent or one occurrence\nChecks already completed:\nRecent changes:\nWorkaround or containment:\nSupporting evidence:\nOperator contact and availability:</pre></div>\n<h3>For an integration issue, also include</h3>\n<ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>API or Webhook operation or event name.</li><li>Request ID, endpoint and timestamp.</li><li>Response status and redacted error body.</li><li>Retry result and affected External ID.</li><li>The first failing system boundary.</li></ul>\n<div class=\"comparison-grid\">\n  <article class=\"comparison-card poor\"><span>Poor request</span><p>“Orders are broken. Please investigate urgently.”</p></article>\n  <article class=\"comparison-card actionable\"><span>Actionable request</span><p>“Production Order 12345 was successfully paid at 10:42 AEST, but no Seller Invoice was created for Seller 789. Two earlier transactions succeeded. Payment reference, Order ID, expected Seller split and completed checks are attached.”</p></article>\n</div>\n","Manage an Active Incident":"\n<p>Assign one incident owner and keep an internal control log. Use the smallest effective containment action while preserving fulfilment, returns, refunds, customer communication and Finance reconciliation.</p><div class=\"incident-status-action\"><div><strong>Check for a wider platform incident</strong><span>Review Marketplacer Status when several users, Sellers or connected workflows are affected.</span></div><a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://status.marketplacer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Marketplacer Status</a></div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Control area</th><th>Record</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Incident owner</td><td>Decision authority, backup and availability</td></tr><tr><td>Impact</td><td>Affected customers, Sellers, Products, Orders and financial records</td></tr><tr><td>Containment</td><td>What was paused, limited or routed manually</td></tr><tr><td>Communication</td><td>Audience, owner, message, cadence and next update</td></tr><tr><td>Evidence</td><td>New affected IDs, logs and timestamps</td></tr><tr><td>Recovery</td><td>Authoritative correction, retest and reconciliation plan</td></tr><tr><td>Exit</td><td>Criteria for removing temporary controls and closing the incident</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Possible containment actions</h3>\n<div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Catalogue</h3><p>Pause one Product range, Seller or Promotion.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Integration</h3><p>Stop one failing worker, Webhook or Seller Invoice delivery path.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Customer journey</h3><p>Limit traffic, payment method or checkout scope.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Finance</h3><p>Hold affected remittance or payout while records are reconciled.</p></article></div>\n<div class=\"copy-template compact\"><div class=\"copy-template-heading\"><strong>Incident status update</strong><span>Use a consistent cadence</span></div><pre>Status:\nBusiness impact:\nCurrent containment:\nRecords affected since the last update:\nInvestigation or recovery progress:\nDecisions required:\nNext update:</pre></div>\n","Handle Integration, Payment and MPay Issues":"\n<div class=\"support-specialist-grid\">\n  <article><h3>APIs and Webhooks</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Operation or event</li><li>Redacted payload or query</li><li>Response and authentication method</li><li>Timestamp and External ID</li><li>Delivery attempts and duplicate handling</li><li>First failing boundary</li></ul></article>\n  <article><h3>MConnect</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Connection status</li><li>Most recent successful task</li><li>Import or task error</li><li>Product or Seller Invoice reference</li><li>Source-platform record</li><li>Selected sync settings and source ownership</li></ul></article>\n  <article><h3>Payment provider</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Customer authorisation or capture</li><li>Storefront checkout result</li><li>Marketplacer Order creation</li><li>Payment refund</li><li>Marketplacer refund record</li><li>Settlement and reconciliation</li></ul></article>\n  <article><h3>MPay</h3><ul class=\"bullet-list\"><li>Seller and payout reference</li><li>Verification or payout stage</li><li>Marketplacer evidence</li><li>Business impact</li><li>Operator checks completed</li><li>Marketplacer Support request</li></ul></article>\n</div>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Identify the financial stage.</strong> “Refund failed” is not specific enough. Separate the Marketplacer refund workflow, customer cash movement, Seller adjustment and settlement result.</div>\n<div class=\"official-resource-grid\"><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator and Seller technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>MConnect</h3><p>Review connection status, scope and errors before escalation.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360012519092-MConnect-Marketplacer-Integrations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open MConnect guidance</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Webhook Retry Policy</h3><p>Confirm which failures are retried and how delivery progresses.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/webhookretries/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Retry Policy</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Technology</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Webhook Deduplication</h3><p>Review duplicate-prevention behaviour.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/webhooks/deduplication/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open Deduplication guide</a>\n    </article><article class=\"official-resource-card\">\n      <div class=\"official-resource-card-top\"><span class=\"resource-tag\">Operator and Finance</span><span class=\"resource-status\">Current official resource</span></div>\n      <h3>Introduction to MPay for Operators</h3><p>Understand MPay responsibilities and the Marketplacer Support route.</p>\n      <a class=\"resource-action\" href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41580327625613-Introduction-to-MPay-for-Operators\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Open MPay guide</a>\n    </article></div>\n","Protect Sensitive Information":"\n<p>Share only the minimum information required to investigate the issue and use an approved secure method for restricted files.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Do not include casually</th><th>Use instead</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Passwords, MFA recovery codes or API secrets</td><td>A description of the authentication method and a redacted key identifier</td></tr><tr><td>Full access tokens or credentials</td><td>Masked values and secure rotation evidence</td></tr><tr><td>Full payment-card or bank information</td><td>Payment-provider references and masked account details</td></tr><tr><td>Unnecessary customer personal data</td><td>Record IDs, masked email addresses and the smallest relevant screenshot</td></tr><tr><td>Unrestricted Production exports</td><td>A filtered and redacted extract containing only affected records</td></tr><tr><td>KYC or identity documents</td><td>The verification reference and approved secure transfer process</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Review screenshots and payloads before attaching them.</strong> Redact secrets, customer data, wholesale values and unrelated records while preserving the evidence needed to investigate.</div>\n","Close, Learn and Maintain Support Readiness":"\n<p>Close the issue only when the expected behaviour or resolution is understood, affected records are reconciled, stakeholders are updated and any temporary control has an explicit outcome.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Incident register field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Support request reference</td><td>Links the internal record to Marketplacer Support</td></tr><tr><td>Issue type and environment</td><td>Supports reporting and trend analysis</td></tr><tr><td>Business impact and affected records</td><td>Preserves the reason and reconciliation scope</td></tr><tr><td>Internal owner</td><td>Keeps Operator accountability clear</td></tr><tr><td>Containment</td><td>Records temporary controls and their removal</td></tr><tr><td>Resolution</td><td>Captures the confirmed result or expected behaviour</td></tr><tr><td>Documentation change</td><td>Prevents repeat confusion</td></tr><tr><td>Retest and closed date</td><td>Confirms recovery and closure</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Operator Support Readiness Checklist</h3>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>A named internal support owner and backup are assigned.</li><li>Seller and customer support routes are documented.</li><li>Marketplacer Support access is confirmed.</li><li>Required Operator Portal permissions are assigned.</li><li>The evidence and Support request templates are available.</li><li>Internal incident priorities and decision authority are agreed.</li><li>Sensitive-data handling rules are understood.</li><li>Escalation contacts and communication owners are current.</li><li>Support and Customer Service handover is complete.</li></ul>\n"},"related":[["marketplacer-resources","Marketplacer Resources"],["operator-resources","Operator Resources"],["integration-troubleshooting","Integration Troubleshooting"],["daily-operations","Daily Marketplace Operations"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"],["go-live","Go-Live"]]}};
